info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued May 29 at 3:45AM CDT until May 29 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM CDT THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog. * WHERE...Southern Lake, Southern Cook and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band and the Grand Portage Reservation. * WHEN...Until 1 PM CDT this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Fog close to Lake Superior may come in waves and visibilities may lift occasionally to a mile or above.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.
